==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Osteotomy
<hw>Os`te*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
dissection or anatomy of bones; osteology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The operation of dividing a bone
or of cutting a piece out of it, -- done to remedy deformity,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osteozoa</ent>⟦br⟧
